  "physical_motivation": {
    "intermediate_seeds": "Seeds of 10^3 M_sun are consistent with Population III remnants in dense nuclear star clusters (Madau & Rees 2001; Devecchi & Volonteri 2009) and fall well below the heavy-seed abundance problem threshold (10^5 M_sun).",
    "mild_super_eddington": "Accretion at 1.5-2.5x Eddington is routinely observed in local ultraluminous X-ray sources (King et al. 2023; Middleton et al. 2015) and confirmed stable over 10^7 yr timescales in radiation-magnetohydrodynamic simulations (Jiang et al. 2019). This is far below the 10x required without TEP."
